<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;font-family:helvetica;font-size:medium;">The purpose of this community is to create and maintain an atmosphere of love, humility, and peace so as to perpetuate unity among Christians and spiritual growth through Jesus Christ our Lord.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This is a community for Christian believers.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Christian</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> being defined by the Nicene Creed.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>This definition is not given so as to exclude anyone from posting, but rather to define the nature of this community.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Nonbelievers are welcome to participate, providing the rules are followed, but it is important to note that this is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> an apologetics board.<br>
<br>
Discussions in the theology/bible study should be founded on the central elements as expressed in the Nicene Creed; topics posted in order to debate against the tenants of the Nicene Creed will be deleted. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:navy;font-family:Helvetica;font-size:medium;">1) Communicate to others with kindness;  No foul or abusive language will be tolerated.<br>
<br>
2) No spamming or trolling; these types of posts may be immediately deleted. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Helvetica;font-size:medium;">Spam includes, but is not limited to:<br>
<br>
*Posts that advertise and/or solicit money from the members of this community.<br>
<br>
*Posts that are duplicated and appear on a variety of similar discussion boards (excluding prayer requests) with no intention of maintaining/following up with later discussion.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:navy;font-family:Helvetica;font-size:medium;">3) Keep signatures small and non-repetitive in threads.<br>
<br>
4) When quoting other members of this community, assign their user name in your posts.<br>
<br>
5) Posting under more than ONE username is not allowed; if there is a valid reason for changing your username, please notify administration.<br>
<br>
6) Engaging in rude behavior will evoke a public warning from administration.  After three warnings, you will be banned from this community.  An appeal for reinstatement may be made after 8 weeks.<br>
<br>
7) Content from this website may not be copied for any reason without the express permission of staff or author of post.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
